Important Commands (Step-by-Step)
🟢 STEP 0: Ready check
whoami
pwd
✔ confirm karo tum admin/root ya ubuntu user ho
________________________________________
📦 1. PACKAGE MANAGEMENT (apt)
🔹 Step 1: Update system
sudo apt update
🧠 Kya hota hai:
•	system ko latest software list milti hai
________________________________________
🔹 Step 2: Install package (nginx)
sudo apt install nginx -y
🔹 Step 3: Check install
nginx -v
✔ agar version aa gaya → success
________________________________________
⚙️ 2. SERVICES (systemctl)
🔹 Step 1: Start nginx
sudo systemctl start nginx
🔹 Step 2: Check status
sudo systemctl status nginx
🟢 Expected:
•	active (running)
________________________________________
🔹 Step 3: Restart service
sudo systemctl restart nginx
________________________________________
🔹 Step 4: Enable (auto start on reboot)
sudo systemctl enable nginx
________________________________________
🧠 3. PROCESSES
🔹 Step 1: Running processes
ps
🔹 Better view:
ps aux
________________________________________
🔹 Live monitoring
top
👉 Exit:
q
________________________________________
🔹 Install htop (easy version)
sudo apt install htop -y
htop
👉 Exit:
F10
________________________________________
🔹 Kill process (practice safe way)
Step 1: find PID
ps aux | grep nginx
Step 2: kill process
kill PID
Force kill:
kill -9 PID
________________________________________
💾 4. DISK USAGE
🔹 System disk
df -h
________________________________________
🔹 Folder size
du -sh /var
________________________________________
📜 5. LOGS
🔹 System logs
journalctl
________________________________________
🔹 Live logs (VERY IMPORTANT DevOps)
sudo tail -f /var/log/syslog
👉 Exit:
CTRL + C
________________________________________
👤 6. USERS & GROUPS
🔹 Create user
sudo useradd devuser
🔹 Set password
sudo passwd devuser
🔹 Create group
sudo groupadd devgroup
🔹 Add user to group
sudo usermod -aG devgroup devuser
________________________________________
🔹 Verify
id devuser
________________________________________
🧰 7. USEFUL COMMANDS
🔹 Print text
echo "Hello DevOps"
________________________________________
🔹 Create file
echo "Hello World" > file.txt
________________________________________
